11/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Tuesday (10 June), the Economy Committee of the Skopje-Sofia-Nish Euro-region initiative held the latest in a series of meetings in the Macedonian capital.
Government experts, customs officials, members of the business community and representatives of the economic chambers of the three countries participated.
The talks focused on promoting the development of small and medium enterprises along Corridor 8.
Participants also reviewed a study on sustainable development through institutionalised cross-border co-operation in the Skopje-Sofia-Nish triangle.
(Makfax - 10/06/03)
